# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# .env.example — copy to .env.local and fill in your values
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# WHAT BELONGS HERE vs. ON CONVEX
#
# Anything prefixed VITE_ ships to the browser (Vite inlines it at build
# time). The CONVEX_DEPLOYMENT line is also read locally — by `npx convex
# dev` to know which deployment to push functions to.
#
# Backend-only secrets (Clerk JWT issuer, Polar API token, Polar webhook
# secret, Stripe key, etc.) DO NOT go in this file. They go on the Convex
# deployment via `npx convex env set NAME value` so they're only visible
# to your Convex functions. See the "Convex deployment env" section at
# the bottom for the full list.
#
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


# ─────────────────── Clerk (auth) — frontend ──────────────────────────
# Get this at https://dashboard.clerk.com → your app → API Keys
# Starts with pk_test_ (dev) or pk_live_ (prod).
VITE_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_c3F1YXJlLWdyb3VwZXItNTcuY2xlcmsuYWNjb3VudHMuZGV2JA


# ─────────────────── Convex (DB + backend) — frontend ─────────────────
# Auto-populated by `npx convex dev` the first time you run it.
# For a local anonymous deployment these point at 127.0.0.1; for a
# Convex Cloud deployment they look like https://xxx.convex.cloud
# and https://xxx.convex.site (the .site URL is where HTTP routes
# like the Polar webhook live).
CONVEX_DEPLOYMENT=dev:strong-dolphin-979|eyJ2MiI6IjFmYWFhNDhhYjYxZTRmOWJhOWZjMGVkMjI2NjI5MmIzIn0=
VITE_CONVEX_URL=http://127.0.0.1:3210
VITE_CONVEX_SITE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:3211


# ─────────────────── App URL (frontend, optional) ─────────────────────
# Used as embed_origin and success_url for Polar checkout. Defaults to
# http://localhost:5173 if unset on the Convex deployment.
# In production this should be your deployed site URL.
# VITE_APP_URL=http://localhost:5173


# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CONVEX DEPLOYMENT ENV — these are NOT set in this file.
# Run `npx convex env set NAME value` for each one.
# Verify with `npx convex env list`.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Required for auth:
#   CLERK_JWT_ISSUER_DOMAIN
#     The Issuer URL of the Clerk JWT template named exactly "convex".
#     Find it in Clerk dashboard → Configure → JWT Templates → convex.
#     Example: https://square-grouper-57.clerk.accounts.dev
#
# Required for live Polar billing (omit any → demo mode kicks in):
#   POLAR_ACCESS_TOKEN
#     Polar dashboard → Settings → Developers → + New Token
#     (scope: checkouts:write). Starts with polar_oat_
#
#   POLAR_PRODUCT_ID_MONTHLY
#     UUID of the Pro Monthly product in Polar.
#
#   POLAR_PRODUCT_ID_YEARLY
#     UUID of the Pro Yearly product in Polar.
#
#   POLAR_WEBHOOK_SECRET
#     Shown once when you create the webhook in Polar.
#     Starts with whsec_
#
# Optional:
#   POLAR_SERVER
#     "sandbox" or "production". Omit for production.
#
#   APP_PUBLIC_URL
#     Your site URL for embed_origin and success_url callbacks.
#     Defaults to http://localhost:5173.
#
# See polar.md for the full Polar setup walkthrough.
